1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,850
Here is the first step toward success.

2
00:00:02,959 --> 00:00:04,370
It's a basic step.

3
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:06,050
It can't be avoided.

4
00:00:06,239 --> 00:00:09,090
Step one, believe in yourself.

5
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:11,170
Believe you can succeed.

6
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:16,209
How to develop the power of belief.

7
00:00:16,209 --> 00:00:20,930
Here are the three guides to acquiring and strengthening the power of belief.

8
00:00:20,930 --> 00:00:22,209
1.

9
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,330
Think success, don't think failure.

10
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:30,850
At work, in your home, substitute success thinking for failure thinking.

11
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:37,249
When you face a difficult situation, think, I'll win, not, I'll probably lose.

12
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:44,050
When you compete with someone else, think, I'm equal to the best, not, I'm outclassed.

13
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:49,410
When opportunity appears, think, I can do it, never I can't.

14
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:54,769
Let the master thought, I will succeed, dominate your thinking process.

15
00:00:55,040 --> 00:01:00,289
Thinking success conditions your mind to create plans that produce success.

16
00:01:00,479 --> 00:01:03,489
Thinking failure does the exact opposite.

17
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:09,489
Failure thinking conditions the mind to think other thoughts that produce failure.

18
00:01:09,489 --> 00:01:11,170
2.

19
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:15,969
Remind yourself regularly that you are better than you think you are.

20
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:18,769
Successful people are not supermen.

21
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:21,969
Success does not require a super intellect.

22
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:25,410
Nor is there anything mystical about success.

23
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,370
And success isn't based on luck.

24
00:01:28,719 --> 00:01:35,009
Successful people are just ordinary folks who have developed belief in themselves and what they do.

25
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:39,410
Never, yes, never sell yourself short.

26
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:41,330
3.

27
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,930
Believe big.

28
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:47,570
The size of your success is determined by the size of your belief.

29
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:51,090
Think little goals and expect little achievements.

30
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:54,289
Think big goals and win big success.

31
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,050
Remember this, too.

32
00:01:56,320 --> 00:02:04,610
Big ideas and big plans are often easier, certainly no more difficult, than small ideas and small plans.

33
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:12,850
Mr. Ralph J. Cordoner, chairman of the board of the General Electric Company, said this to a leadership conference.

34
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:19,009
We need from every man who aspires to leadership, for himself and his company,

35
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:23,810
a determination to undertake a personal program of self-development.

36
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:27,090
Nobody is going to order a man to develop.

37
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:34,209
Whether a man lags behind or moves ahead in his specialty is a matter of his own personal application.

38
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:38,209
This is something which takes time, work, and sacrifice.

39
00:02:38,479 --> 00:02:40,290
Nobody can do it for you.

40
00:02:40,959 --> 00:02:44,130
Mr. Cordoner's advice is sound and practical.

41
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:45,090
Live it.

